name: youtubereporting
title: YouTube Reporting API
description: Schedules reporting jobs containing your YouTube Analytics data and downloads the resulting bulk data reports in the form of CSV files.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc:
A token to retrieve next page of results.
Pass this value in the
ListReportsRequest.page_token
field in the subsequent call to `ListReports` method to retrieve the next
page of results.

fields.name: reports
fields.desc: The list of report types.

fields.name: resourceName
fields.desc: Name of the media resource.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the report type (max. 100 characters).

fields.name: systemManaged
fields.desc:
True if this a system-managed report type; otherwise false. Reporting jobs
for system-managed report types are created automatically and can thus not
be used in the `CreateJob` method.

fields.name: deprecateTime
fields.desc: The date/time when this report type was/will be deprecated.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the report type (max. 100 characters).

schemas.name: Report
schemas.desc:
A report's metadata including the URL from which the report itself can be
downloaded.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The server-generated ID of the report.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc:
The end of the time period that the report instance covers. The value is
exclusive.

fields.name: jobExpireTime
fields.desc: The date/time when the job this report belongs to will expire/expired.

fields.name: downloadUrl
fields.desc: The URL from which the report can be downloaded (max. 1000 characters).

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc:
The start of the time period that the report instance covers. The value is
inclusive.

fields.name: createTime
fields.desc: The date/time when this report was created.

fields.name: jobId
fields.desc: The ID of the job that created this report.

schemas.name: Empty

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc:
A token to retrieve next page of results.
Pass this value in the
ListReportTypesRequest.page_token
field in the subsequent call to `ListReportTypes` method to retrieve the next
page of results.

fields.name: reportTypes
fields.desc: The list of report types.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc:
A token to retrieve next page of results.
Pass this value in the
ListJobsRequest.page_token
field in the subsequent call to `ListJobs` method to retrieve the next
page of results.

fields.name: jobs
fields.desc: The list of jobs.

schemas.name: Job
schemas.desc: A job creating reports of a specific type.

fields.name: createTime
fields.desc: The creation date/time of the job.

fields.name: reportTypeId
fields.desc:
The type of reports this job creates. Corresponds to the ID of a
ReportType.

fields.name: expireTime
fields.desc:
The date/time when this job will expire/expired. After a job expired, no
new reports are generated.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the job (max. 100 characters).

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The server-generated ID of the job (max. 40 characters).

fields.name: systemManaged
fields.desc:
True if this a system-managed job that cannot be modified by the user;
otherwise false.

methods.name: create
methods.desc: Creates a job and returns it.

optinalQueryParams.desc:
The content owner's external ID on which behalf the user is acting on. If
not set, the user is acting for himself (his own channel).

pathParams.name: jobId
pathParams.desc: The ID of the job to delete.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageSize
optinalQueryParams.desc:
Requested page size. Server may return fewer jobs than requested.
If unspecified, server will pick an appropriate default.

optinalQueryParams.desc:

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken
optinalQueryParams.desc:
A token identifying a page of results the server should return. Typically,
this is the value of
ListReportTypesResponse.next_page_token
returned in response to the previous call to the `ListJobs` method.

optinalQueryParams.name: includeSystemManaged
optinalQueryParams.desc:
If set to true, also system-managed jobs will be returned; otherwise only
user-created jobs will be returned. System-managed jobs can neither be
modified nor deleted.

methods.name: list
methods.desc:
Lists reports created by a specific job.
Returns NOT_FOUND if the job does not exist.

optinalQueryParams.name: createdAfter
optinalQueryParams.desc: If set, only reports created after the specified date/time are returned.

optinalQueryParams.name: startTimeAtOrAfter
optinalQueryParams.desc:
If set, only reports whose start time is greater than or equal the
specified date/time are returned.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken
optinalQueryParams.desc:
A token identifying a page of results the server should return. Typically,
this is the value of
ListReportsResponse.next_page_token
returned in response to the previous call to the `ListReports` method.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageSize
optinalQueryParams.desc:
Requested page size. Server may return fewer report types than requested.
If unspecified, server will pick an appropriate default.

optinalQueryParams.name: onBehalfOfContentOwner
optinalQueryParams.desc:
The content owner's external ID on which behalf the user is acting on. If
not set, the user is acting for himself (his own channel).

optinalQueryParams.name: startTimeBefore
optinalQueryParams.desc:
If set, only reports whose start time is smaller than the specified
date/time are returned.
